title follow + refs: graph navigation commands
edge explains commit:08653c770662337db924495fc4cd021e020e1573

Two commands make the three core patterns easy:

- follow: read a note, resolve every edge, show what's at the other end.
  Makes 'one note → many refs' visible in one command.
  Makes planning graphs walkable — follow HEAD shows the plan.

- refs: reverse lookup. Given any object, find every note that points at it.
  Makes 'one ref → many notes' explicit — not just context (which walks
  the tree) but ALL inbound edges from anywhere in the graph.

Together they give bidirectional graph traversal with zero dependencies
beyond git and bash. follow = outbound, refs = inbound.
